{"Title": "The European road safety decision support system on risks and measures", "Year": 2019, "Source": "Accid. Anal. Prev.", "Volume": "125", "Issue": null, "Art.No": null, "PageStart": 344, "PageEnd": 351, "CitedBy": 4, "DOI": "10.1016/j.aap.2018.08.005", "Link": "https://www.scopus.com/inward/record.uri?partnerID=HzOxMe3b&scp=85051642327&origin=inward", "Abstract": "\u00a9 2018 Elsevier LtdThe European Road Safety Decision Support System (roadsafety-dss.eu) is an innovative system providing the available evidence on a broad range of road risks and possible countermeasures. This paper describes the scientific basis of the DSS. The structure underlying the DSS consists of (1) a taxonomy identifying risk factors and measures and linking them to each other, (2) a repository of studies, and (3) synopses summarizing the effects estimated in the literature for each risk factor and measure, and (4) an economic efficiency evaluation instrument (E3-calculator). The DSS is implemented in a modern web-based tool with a highly ergonomic interface, allowing users to get a quick overview or go deeper into the results of single studies according to their own needs.", "AuthorKeywords": ["Cost-Benefit", "Effectiveness", "Online system", "Review", "Road risks", "Road safety countermeasures"], "IndexKeywords": ["Cost benefits", "Economic efficiency", "Effectiveness", "Innovative systems", "Road risk", "Road safety", "Scientific basis", "Web-based tools", "Accidents, Traffic", "Built Environment", "Cost-Benefit Analysis", "Data Collection", "Decision Support Techniques", "Humans", "Risk Factors", "Safety"], "DocumentType": "Journal", "PublicationStage": null, "OpenAccess": 2, "EID": "2-s2.0-85051642327", "SubjectAreas": [["Human Factors and Ergonomics", "SOCI", "3307"], ["Safety, Risk, Reliability and Quality", "ENGI", "2213"], ["Public Health, Environmental and Occupational Health", "MEDI", "2739"]], "AuthorData": {"56259198500": {"Name": "Martensen H.", "AuthorID": "56259198500